						<summary>

						<p>On a slab in the <hi rend="italic">Kalamdoḍḍi</hi> of Karrapu Sesha Reddi.</p>						

						<p>The record is dated Śaka 1461, <hi rend="italic">Vikāri, Jyēshṭha,</hi> ba. 30, corresponding to 1539 A.D., June 16.</p>						

						<p>Records the construction of a step-well and the grant of some land for worship and offerings to god Veṅkaṭādri of Iñjēḍu by Pāṇayya, son of Kēsavarāju of Iñjēḍu, and the <hi rend="italic">sthala-karaṇam</hi> of Iñjēḍu.</p>						

						</summary>
